messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /printshops/{printShopId}/reviews/{reviewId}

All HTTP methods acceptable?
- No

Per-method acceptability (based on the code, not assumptions):
- HEAD: No
- POST: No
- OPTIONS: No
- TRACE: No
- GET: No
- PUT: Yes
- DELETE: Yes
- PATCH: No

Explanation:
- The deletePrintShopReview method is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{printShopId}/reviews/{reviewId}", method = RequestMethod.DELETE), so the endpoint path is exactly /printshops/{printShopId}/reviews/{reviewId} and it explicitly accepts DELETE.
- The editPrintShopReview method uses @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{printShopId}/reviews/{reviewId}", method = RequestMethod.PUT), so the same path explicitly accepts PUT.
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping that would change the prefix, and no other explicit @RequestMapping for this exact path and other HTTP methods are present in the provided source, so only PUT and DELETE are accepted according to the code.
- I did not assume framework behaviors (such as automatic HEAD/OPTIONS handling) â€” only explicit RequestMapping(method=...) annotations were considered.
